# CODEOWNERS — automatic review assignment
#
# Syntax: <path-glob>  <owner1> <owner2> ...
# Owners are GitHub usernames (@user) or team handles (@org/team).
# Last matching pattern wins. Order matters.
#
# Rules for AI agents and humans:
#   1. Every PR must auto-assign at least one CODEOWNER for each touched area.
#   2. If a path has no owner, the global fallback (last line) catches it.
#   3. To change ownership, open a PR modifying THIS file; the existing
#      owners of the touched area must approve.
#   4. Keep this file SHORT. Mirror responsibilities defined in CLASS_MAP.md
#      and GOVERNANCE.md.

# ─── Global fallback (lowest priority — must come first) ─────────────
*                                       @[ORG]/engineering-leads

# ─── Documentation ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
